============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is supply and demand?
A1: Supply and demand determines prices: higher demand or
     lower supply raises prices; lower demand or higher
     supply lowers prices. Equilibrium is where both curves
     intersect.

Q2: What is the internet?
A2: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q3: What is the Renaissance?
A3: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q4: What is capitalism?
A4: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q5: What is DNA?
A5: DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) is a double helix molecule
     that carries genetic information. It consists of base
     pairs: adenine-thymine and guanine-cytosine.

